tussocky
Homonym Number:
Word Class: adjective
Sense Number:  1
Definition:[of land, country, pasture, property etc] clothed with native tussocks.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: includes sense of being tussock-like
